From Ed McClanahan Subject Re on ATI Ultra w Nanao Keith Mancus writes reference to running ATI's Install Program and using its functions to position size images at various resolutions I thought this was a neat feature until I noticed that when an image is re sized the scanning frequency is necessarily This causes digital multiscan monitors like my MAG to get confused as to which mode to use if the frequency gets too far from the standard For this reason I use the factory defaults for position size on the ATI card and adjust each mode individually only the first time at the The MAG and many other multiscan monitors has have the ability to recall these settings the next time each mode is detected Edward McClanahan